                </div>
                
                <p>
                    Throughout all of the projects I did in college, for work, or on the side, there was often an element of the project that used a tool or language that I had not yet worked with. Since these projects often required that one element be done in a specific way, I was always motivated to learn the necessary tool or language in order to not compromise on the end goal. The most common occurrence of needing to learn something new and quick for a project was with 3d modelling. <br><br>3d modelling is a vast landscape of knowledge, experience, and nifty tricks. Whenever it was required of me, I could dive into a new modelling software without having previously done a similar asset and could still manage to get that asset completed within its objectives and constraints. Of course, these projects only scraped the basics of 3d modelling itself but my determined acquirement of these skills as well as my enthusiasm and patience for learning is something I hope to take with me in every project I work on.
                </p>
            </div>
        
